So whats your favorite original soundtrack?
Mines a toss up between Red Alert 2's soundtrack and Trigun Happy Doughnut Pack.
I guess you could just post your favorite any kind of soundtrack but non-original soundtracks just end up sounding like Mix CDs IMO.

item.title: Your Favorite Original Soundtrack
item.dc:creator: Winged_One
item.description:
k3nny1550:

I thought the film was generally mediocre. I mean, the ending made no sense- The digital girl comes into reality with him. How the fuck did she get a host body?

Oh wait, she’s explicitly stated to be the last member of a digital civilization that apparently is just that cool. They dedicate ten minutes to explaining them, and just kinda are like Get over it. We can’t figure out a better way to write this in, so just enjoy the fucking movie and forget it!

I’m not slamming the film too hard, it was never boring and always had something new to throw at the viewer, but it wasn’t good. You know what I mean?

As for the Legacy OST, I liked “The Game Has Changed.” That and “Derezzed” were the standout tracks. I’ll have to listen to more of the album.

Thanks, cock.

Read full topic
